reviews.review_text:
Excellent show & mastering Patch Info:
(FOB) Beyer M160 + (1) Senn 421 -> Cassette Master -> FLAC (shnid=109804) suplies:
Tuning through Ramble On Rose
Drums (3:20 - 3:53)
Day Job (0:00 - 006) (2:37 - end of track)

Thanks again Charlie!  

I have always enjoyed listening to the second set of this show; I hope you do to!

Nice to have Like Jack' O said, its a good sounding audience recording through most of the first set, when it gets to the soundboard portion its worth it, firing on all cylinders. 

Second set is really varied and well performed on a tour that was hit or miss. Nice long post drums. This is the only available board for this show so go ahead and grab it while you can. 

Thanks CM

Another Fine, Fine Day!! I love cycling through the "anniversary" of shows and reminiscing about the days past w/ the Boys! Indy was super fun (saw 6/30/84, 85 and 88...) and a great little venue; was actually a tennis center as many have noted; This really captures the sound of this show well; perfect summer day, show wasn't even sold out (as was still common at times in 84) and it was a Saturday! 

Listening to this now w/ headphones and just caught Lost Sailor tease before Esau! Great stuff...

beautiful sound, beautiful show an easy 5 in my mind for cumulative excellence; first set is hot and second set opens up like wine with a little air... ending seemed just a little rushed after stella blue, but so what?
